\par\pard\plain \fi360\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 tenth.}{\f0\fs24  This is a one-time tithe of the booty (cf. Num. 31:25\endash 41), not an annual tithe to the priest (cf. Lev. 27:30\endash 33; Num. 18:21). Tithing is an old and ancient practice in the biblical world (see 7:2). Kedorlaomer\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s tribute is paid as a tithe to the Lord! With the institution of monarchy, a greedy king demands the annual tithe along with the priest (1 Sam. 8:15, 17). The text does not suggest that Melchizedek has come to collect his tithe, though some foist that suggestion upon it. Melchizedek celebrates Abraham as God\u8217\'92s warrior and blesses him. Abraham recognizes Melchizedek as the legitimate priest and king of his God.}
